title: Grateful Dead Live at Winterland Arena on 1974-10-18
description:
Set 1

Around & Around, Sugaree, Beer Barrel Polka Tuning, Mexicali Blues, Peggy-O, Beat It On Down The Line, Brown Eyed Women, Cumberland Blues, El Paso, Tennessee Jed, Jack Straw, Row Jimmy, Weather Report Suite Prelude-> Weather Report Suite Part 1-> Let It Grow

Set 2

Phil & Ned-> Dark Star-> Drums-> Dark Star-> Morning Dew

Set 3

Promised Land-> Bertha-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Ship of Fools, Not Fade Away-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> One More Saturday Night, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
Shines Thru The Rains This show i attended and will have to admit I am intrigued by this show enough that I will listen to most any version of it that suits my fancy...

And this presentation suits my fancy big time. 

That night had amusing sonic and technical difficulties -- such as previously stated on my reviews of this show on Archives.org.

The Phil & Ned is oh so supreme and the rest you get sublime.


Might consider this show one of the most supreme from on high.

Ahh, Somehow this show always shines thru the reigns.

And this GEM reveals the true sanctity:

Such the Remnant of our clingingest belief.

Relief.

Still, tonite, one of the greatest shows i have ever heard.


52 out of 5 Stars.


!

historians start here? ends here? stay here... try and figure it out.  Wait - they did figure it out.  Its the GRATEFUL DEAD  - the floor is full of the melted minds-of all of you- we have arrived-  at terrapin

52 out of 5 stars for the hell of it. For you Evan

wow tops 4 sound quality , easytopten ever, "reely" reels , reel nice sweet deep wide, clarity
check out morning dew..........................
separation on cumbeland blues is tasty
this is perhaps a top 3 recording ever , yes even for the dead, all 6 of my speakers are also amazed.

Seastones Ned does not brings much to the table in Dead's ensemble format. (He sounds like an atonal nightmare Jerry has to coral)
I prefer the lighter mellower sound of just the regular rotation tunes they played on this run without NED.
But make no mistake the intensity level is way up for this - Seastones > Dark Star > Dew-
You can't out 'space' Garcia!!!
I have no words Absolutely amazing show and amazing recording.  Wake of the Flood material at it's finest.

Holy bejeezus! I didn't think any Morning Dew could top the intensity of 9.18.87. I was wrong. Dead wrong. Ok, this little Dew right here may not be quite as intense, but it does have a major something MSG Dew lacks.... PHIL!!! Dammers I love me some Dew!
Epic Super clean quality. Love the warmth and clarity of reels. Epic Grateful Dead.
Morning Dew My #1 is this one. Love how it's shot in the GD Movie. Post-hiatus, my fave is 4/6/82 Spectrum.
Top notch So crisp and clean.. A prefect mix... These last shows of 74 are SO SO GOOD... The best of 74 imho..
